1.Dynamic typing

when we create a variable without mention data type it is called dynamic typing
IN
python--> n=5
2.Static typing
when we create a variable and mention is data type is called static typing
IN
c--> int n=5

3.Dynamic Binding
a=5
print(a)
a='nitish'
print(a)

output:
5
nitish

in python if we declare a variable it can be change to any data type so this behaviour is called dynamic binding

the opposite is static binding
int a=5
printf(a)
int a='nitish'
printf(a)
error


4.create variable
a,b,c=1,2,4
a=b=c=5
print(a,b,c)

